Project Recap

The Question
Are there any SNPs (genotype) that are significant predictors for TCR diversity (phenotype)?

How can we model TCR diversity given a set of genotypes and phenotypes?

Genetic Ancestry: Statistical Methods

  • Sub machine learning task to extract ancestry proportions

ADMIXTURE UCLA

  • Global Ancestry (proportion of ancestries over entire genome) and Model-based (ancestry coefficients as parameters of statistical model)
  • Bayesian, Monte Carlo Markov Chain model
  • assume K populations
  • \( q_{ik} \) is kth population's contribution fraction to ith person's genome
  • \( f_{jk} \) is the frequency for allele 1 of jth SNP in kth population
  • goal is to determine \( q_{ik} \) and \( f_{jk} \) to maximize likelihood

  • fast convergence

PCA

  • dimension reduction
  • variance projected into lower dimensions of PCs
  • accounts for population stratification
  • plink has option for PCA

Genetic Ancestry: ADMIXTURE Method 1, Unsupervised Learning

  • we don't know K
  • no reference populations
  • cross validation to determine K

Genetic Ancestry: ADMIXTURE Method 1, Unsupervised Learning

  • resulting proportions with K = 2

Genetic Ancestry: ADMIXTURE Method 2, Supervised Learning

  • Data Set Expansion
    • 15 samples from larger study of 129 individuals with unknown ancestry
    • 540147 SNPs from chr 1-22
    • Merge with 1000 Genome reference genomes of 207 individuals of CEU and YRI ancestries
    • 81260710 SNPs from chr 1-22
  • Methods
    1. extract genotypes from larger sample (129 samples)
    2. reverse orientation of SNPs to forward strand with snpFlip
    3. subset 1000 reference genomes for CEU and YRI populations
    4. plink filtering
      • exclude ambiguous SNPs
      • bi-allelic SNPs, remove duplicate SNPs

  • MAF 0.05
  • genotyping rate 0.02
  • LD pruning
  • Feed into ADMIXTURE
  • New Data Set for ADMIXTURE
    • n: 336
    • p: 62674
    • K = 2

ADMIXTURE Method 2: Supervised Learning

  • assume K = 2
  • reference populations are input
  • comparison of standard errors from bootstrap show Unsupervise Learning is less confident

plink PCA

  • plink outputs eigenvalues and eigenvectors

plink PCA

  • PC1 and PC2 may be sufficient

Conclusions and Next Steps

  • Limited data shows rs1052406 is likely significant
  • Supervised Learning approach with ADMIXTURE
  • PC1 and PC2 in PCA can be used

Next Steps

  1. Incorporate ancestry findings into lasso regression
  2. Comparison of ADMIXTURE-lasso vs PCA-lasso implementations
